TextChange: A major issue today in society is that of mental health, it's something we fail to address and are even worse at treating.  In the news, we see horrible headlines on a regular basis from school shootings, to those ending their lives in awful ways.  The question always arises, what could have been done to reach out to these people and how could we have saved them.  The reality is, our mental health system in this country is in shambles.  Not from the prespctive that it does not work, but from the prespective of we do not give people an easy way to reach out for help nor do we encourage those who we do find to be troubles to seek out help.  It's something that's been a constant issue in our society for decades, and every tragic event that has occured, made famous in the news is yet another reason as why we need to try to grow as a society, and reach out to those in needs.
